  "commit_message": "Ensure `@source` globs ending in `**/*` preserve dynamic path segments to avoid scanning too many files (#20217)\n\nThis PR fixes an issue where we were over-scanning because we lost\npattern information when a `@source` ended in `**/*` and contained other\ndynamic parts in the glob pattern.\n\nNoticed this while debugging and working on #20214. Let's say you have\nthe following:\n```css\n@source './blog/*/foo/bar/baz/**/*';\n```\n\nWe make sure that folders or patterns ending in `**/*` are converted to\n\"au",
